Property worth millions of shillings was reduced to ashes after fire gutted down one of the busiest ‘nyama-choma’ joints along the Nairobi-Nakuru highway. During the 2am incident at Fly-Over trading centre, a herd of sheep waiting for slaughter was burnt to death. ALSO READ:

Three children die after house catches fire Runyenjes The incident left up to 100 people jobless and destroyed 20 businesses, mainly those dealing in roast meat around the busy trading centre. According to witnesses, the 2am fire started in one of the butcheries before spreading.